No one talks about how during the Bosnian war there was a 3rd state called "Autonomous Province of Western Bosnia" which was basically a liquor and chocolate biscuit company going rogue and proclaiming independence as a corporation-state that its director was running like a cult.

So we have the Bosnian mujahedeen getting weapons smuggled from Indonesia's Ministry of Forestry, the Serbian ultranationalist militia... oh here is also the separatist BioShock Ayn Rand Mr. House libertarian free city-state controlled by the confectionery factory...  Makes sense

Dmitry Galkovsky on Roman funeral practices, translated from Russian by me (from livejournal blogpost number 739). One will notice how there is a direct link between these traditions and the scene of the gravediggers in Shakespeare's Hamlet joking over the graves that they dig.
yes lol

NB, but when the first gravedigger tells the second "go, get thee to Yaughan, fetch me a stoup of liquor", Yaughan is not a local inn as supposed, but etymologically derived from "Satya Yuga" ("Satyan-Yughan") and the liquor is the ephedric Soma of the gods, granting immortality.
